[4] Australia (New South Wales)
Date: 22 Dec 2015
Source: St. Marys Star [edited]
http://www.stmarysstar.com.au/story/3597825/nsw-health-warns-of-measles-outbreak/?cs=1508


NSW Health warns of measles outbreak
---------------------------
An infant in western Sydney has been diagnosed with measles after an adult contracted the disease during a trip to Singapore. The child was too young to have been vaccinated.

NSW Health communicable diseases branch director Vicky Sheppeard said people need to be aware of the symptoms of measles in the coming weeks, especially those if they who have been in contact with areas the adult visited while infectious.

He attended retail outlets at Parramatta, Wentworthville, Rouse Hill and Kings Langley on 26 and 27 Nov 2015.

The man was at 2 medical centres at Castle Hill and Carlingford 28-30 Nov 2015 and was at Blacktown Hospital's emergency department on 30 Nov 2015.

"These cases signal that a measles outbreak could begin in Sydney in the coming days," Dr Sheppeard said.

"Susceptible people, such as infants under 12 months of age, and older children and adults who have not received 2 doses of measles vaccine, should be on the lookout for symptoms, particularly in the common week."

