[5] Australia (South Australia)
Date: 8 Dec 2015
Source: 9 News [edited]
http://www.9news.com.au/health/2015/12/08/01/55/measles-alert-issued-after-confirmed-case-in-adelaides-northeast


Measles alert issued after confirmed case in Adelaide's northeast
------------------
SA Health has urged students to be immunised against measles.

A measles alert has been issued for Adelaide's northeast after an infected child attended 2 different schools over the past week.

SA Health confirmed that a 12-year-old girl contracted the illness and was contagious when she attended Ardtornish Primary School at St Agnes and Modbury High School at Modbury between 30 Nov and 4 Dec 2015.

The girl had recently travelled to Bali, SA Health Chief Public Health Officer Professor Paddy Phillips said.

Anyone who attended the schools at the same time as the girl should be alert for symptoms including fever, cough, sore eyes and a blotchy rash, Professor Phillips said.

He also urged others to ensure they were immunised against measles.

The full alert is available on the SA Health website.

